  "url": "https://www.tamilmirror.lk/\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd/\u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1-\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf-\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bc1-\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc7-\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1/175-299800",
  "time_ut": 1657050700,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc7 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The central government is just having fun",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The general secretary of Renaissance Dravidian Development Association (MDMU) Vaiko, who has issued a strong condemnation regarding the arrest of Indian fishermen from Rameswaram by the Sri Lankan Navy, has said that it is an injustice to the fishermen of Tamil Nadu that the central government is making fun of Sri Lanka without condemning it.",
        "\"The case filed in the Madras High Court seeking the release of 68 fishermen from Tamil Nadu imprisoned in Sri Lanka was heard in the last week of March in a bench comprising Chief Justice Munishwarnath Bhandari and Justice Bharata Chakraborty.",
        "The judges then said that the ongoing arrest of Tamil Nadu fishermen and confiscation of their boats by the Sri Lankan Navy has become an ongoing story.",
        "In this situation, they ordered the Indian Ministry of External Affairs to take steps to release the 68 Tamil Nadu fishermen who were arrested by the Sri Lankan Navy.",
        "Even after this, the Sri Lankan Navy continued to arrest Indian fishermen, 12 fishermen each on April 2nd and July 1st, and arrested 24 people. He pointed out that 5 fishermen were arrested on July 4.",
        "The Madhya Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) government putting pressure on the Sri Lankan government and making fun of it without condemning it is an injustice done to the fishermen of Tamil Nadu. When will the Sri Lankan government's atrocity of arresting Tamil Nadu fishermen entering Indian waters and imprisoning them in Sri Lankan jails come to an end?\" Vaiko asked."
      ],
